  "title": "ESPC Engineer | 5 Days | Up to $5000 | 9755",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role: ESPC Engineer</strong></p><p><strong>Industry: Facilities services / Energy</strong></p><p><strong>Location: Near Tai Seng MRT | Site</strong></p><p><strong>5 days | Mon-Fri: 9am to 6pm </strong></p><p><strong>Salary: $4000 - $5000</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Bachelor’s degree in Electrical/Controls/Electronics Engineering</strong></li><li><strong>Relevant experience/ experience in ACMV design/controls is a plus</strong></li></ol><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Perform energy audits of energy usages and systems at site</li><li>Analyse data collected and to identify energy improvement opportunities</li><li>Design and select engineering systems or optimization plans that best fit the project requirement / goals</li><li>Participate in tender preparations including technical calculations, equipment selection or system design, costing and any other preparatory works for the bid</li><li>Testing and commission of system</li><li>Fine tuning works to meet targeted or committed efficiency/savings</li><li>Energy savings/efficiency monitoring and reports preparation</li><li>Work along with teams (or independently when necessary) to derive root cause of technical issues and resolution</li><li>Provide Green Mark or equivalent standards consultancy services</li><li>Maintain high standard of service delivery and customer satisfaction</li><li>Maintain good communication with team members to ensure successful implementation of project</li><li>To excel in this job, the candidate will require a high level of organization, creativity, attention to detail, and engineering knowledge to successfully perform design, engineering and field start up tasks for System Integration in Electrical Controls for building M&E systems.</li></ul><p>Tai Jia Seng Reg No: R26159755</p><p>The Supreme Hr Advisory Pte Ltd EA No: 14C7279</p>",
